{
  "texts": [
    "Iris utilises a unique representation called fingerprint (Wu et al. 2018), which is a vector characterising the most meaningful words and their synonyms extracted from the abstract.",
    "In the second group, Covidence and EPPI-Reviewer adopt a BoW representation, while PICOPortal uses both BoW and the BioBERT embeddings (Lee et al. 2020).",
    "Finally, Colandr uses both word2vec (Mikolov et al. 2013) and GloVe (Pennington et al. 2014) embeddings.",
    "Overall, much like other NLP applications, these tools are evolving from traditional text representations like BoW to a range of more modern word and sentence embeddings.",
    "Human interaction: We identified three main types of interfaces."
  ]
}